#5805
The Path of Enlightenment: Combat~
There will always be someone or something against you. Always. Now that you
are prepared, you may face your first foe- the nightmare leech. It is a wary
foe, and will not attack you, but it must be overcome to continue eastward. 
Use 'consider' to tell how strong a foe is compared to you, and 'kill <target>'
to initate combat. If you need to, 'flee' to another room and 'rest' to
regenerate some hit points. At the end of combat 'get all corpse' and see what
you find.
~
